The paper discusses the control and controllability of complex networks, which involves understanding the network topology and the dynamical laws that govern the interactions between components. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including social and information networks (cs.SI), systems and control (cs.SY), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), dynamical systems (cs.DS), and machine learning (cs.LG).
